13.3.15
=======

[PERFORMANCE] Due to situations of high cpu usage when typing continuously,
              the user is now allowed to disable the contribution annotations
              to gain a better performance.

[REGRESSION] Only the session host can invite other users.
             This was neccessary to gain more stability during the invitation process.

[FEATURE] New color management which tries to ensure that users always get the same colors in their sessions,
          independent of who started the session in the first place. To achieve this,
          the freedom of choosing any RGB color was restricted to a five-color-mode.

[FEATURE] Saros has got a 1-to-1 chat enabling a direct communication without the need of opening a session

[FEATURE] Change background color of chat input field if chat is not available
[FEATURE] #3088047 use the MUC service of the currently logged in XMPP
[FEATURE] Visual notification about new Chat entries
[UI] provide better error messages if MUC connection failed
[FIX] #3589970 Session chat can be closed but never be reopened
[FIX] #3588568 Chat contents get lost during session invitation
[FIX] #3572488 Fix annoying chat replay
[FIX] #3573784 Switching followee's active file moves
[FIX] #3589495 Chat display does not properly update its contents

[GUI] changed the progress report for an outgoing project negotiation
[GUI] session invitation no longer reports progress
      Since synchronisation progress cannot be measured during the invitation process,
      the report of it is useless and so it has been removed.
[GUI] always show the exit session dialog if left alone in session
[UI]  disabled copy feature
      When choosing a local project as the incoming project's destination
      an obsolete copy feature has been removed. Choose "new project" to make a copy.
[UI]  Show the configuration wizard when connecting with no account
[FIX] #3390825 Sharing Large projects result in OOM Exception
[FIX] user could edit files while the session is blocked
[FIX] Fix repainting of SimpleRoundedComposite
[FIX] #3439301 Trailing whitespaces break the session
[FIX] #3512780 Getting Started not noticeable enough
[FIX] #3572490 Not-so-smart pre-selection in "Add Projects" dialog
[FIX] #3458952 File changes during Invitation corrupts session
[FIX] Not all changed files were saved before the project archive was
[FIX] #3572485 Buddy-independent actions are shown in context menu
[FIX] #3511072 Leave session needs a different icon  as stop session
[FIX] #3500362 No feedback if sync has finished
[FIX] do not add a default nickname for new subscriptions
[FIX] do not allow a resource qualified JID to be added as a roster
[FIX] The block() and unblock() methods in the EditorManager. 
      This patch prevents the sending of TextEditActivites while the session
      is stopped via the StopManager.
[FIX] #3572498: Deactivate "Add to Saros Session" for read-only users
[FIX] send wrong presence type on subscription cancellation
[FIX] do not allow to start and stop a session at the same time
[FIX] fixed non modal dialog handling
      The wizard for adding a project to a session had a bug which
      caused the GUI to crash occasionally.
[FIX] canceling an invitation caused all outstanding invitations to abort
[FIX] Wizard closing dialog
      During the invitation a dialog opened up allowing the cancelation after
      the invitation has already been accepted. The error messages have been shifted to show up after the wizard finished.
